$ SAS: proc sql - select
@ select


{ Format columns

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/sql/select/format-column.sas||

}
{ Keyword calculated

  The *non-ANSI* keyword `calculated` can be used to refer to a previously calucated value in select statement:
  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/sql/select/calculated.sas||

}
{ Where contains

  `contains` can be used like `like` in ANSI SQL. `contains` can be abbreviated with the question mark (`?`):
  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/sql/select/where/contains.sas||

}
{ flow

  With `flow`, a maximum width can be set for a column:

  gh|about-SAS|/programming/proc/sql/select/flow.sas||

}

